        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 24 at 1:23AM CDT by NWS Norman OK</headline>
        <description>At 123 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles northwest of Tushka, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Atoka, Stringtown, Tushka, Lane, McGee Creek Lake, Boggy Depot Park,
and southwestern Atoka Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
